subSubSection.paragraph:
Vernacular name
. – “Dedal” (CARDOSO JÚNIOR, 1905; 
HENRIQUES, 1896
; BARBOSA, 1961; LEYENS & LOBIN, 1995; 
FIGUEIREDO, 1995
) a Portuguese word meaning “thimble”, the colour adjectives “branco” (white) or “azul” (blue) is sometimes added to the name.

Notes
. – Until now, the populations from W São Nicolau were traditionally identified as 

C. jacobaea

(COUTINHO, 1914; CHEVALIER, 1935; 
SUNDING, 1973
, 
1982
; 
ERIKSSON et al. 1974
, 
1979
; 
NOGUEIRA, 1976
; HANSEN & SUNDING, 1985, 1993; RUSTAN & BROCHMANN, 1993; 
GOMES et al., 1995a
; LEYENS & LOBIN, 1995; 
FIGUEIREDO, 1995
; 
SÁNCHEZ-PINTO et al., 2005
) but some authors have also recognized the presence of 

C. bravensis

in this region (see under 

C. bravensis

).
